WEBVTT

00:00:06.100 --> 00:00:12.100
(September 28, 2025)

00:00:24.690 --> 00:00:25.760
Yokoi, your turn!

00:00:25.810 --> 00:00:29.020
Hey, don't drag Minato into
this weird word game.

00:00:40.150 --> 00:00:41.950
- That's amazing!
- Here, Minato, you take it.

00:00:42.210 --> 00:00:45.850
- Let's play "don't let the spark go out."
- You're on!

00:00:47.040 --> 00:00:48.040
Don't move.

00:00:48.870 --> 00:00:50.650
Okay, looking good.

00:00:53.510 --> 00:00:56.315
(Out for a walk) (Happy 20th!)
Stop taking pictures, it's embarrassing!

00:00:56.340 --> 00:00:57.340
Ah.

00:00:58.550 --> 00:01:00.060
To celebrate Minato's birthday...

00:01:00.110 --> 00:01:01.790
and our first drink together. Cheers!

00:01:06.660 --> 00:01:09.920
We actually took quite a few. What if
we held a photo exhibition just for us?

00:01:10.340 --> 00:01:11.340
Just for the two of us?

00:01:12.300 --> 00:01:14.750
We can decorate the room with these.

00:01:15.110 --> 00:01:16.520
And we'll be the only audience.

00:02:25.100 --> 00:02:27.099
"Countdown To Yes"

00:02:27.100 --> 00:02:31.099
(Minato: I have something to tell you.)

00:02:31.100 --> 00:02:33.500
(Episode 8)

00:02:33.550 --> 00:02:35.480
Instead of dwelling on our past...

00:02:36.670 --> 00:02:38.620
I should focus on what's between us.

00:02:41.430 --> 00:02:42.780
I've thought about it...

00:02:43.870 --> 00:02:45.570
But...

00:02:51.100 --> 00:02:55.500
(Minato: I want copies of the photos too.)
(Minato: The ones from the beach.)

00:02:59.250 --> 00:03:00.480
He's so casual about it.

00:03:27.070 --> 00:03:28.270
Meanwhile, I'm...

00:03:28.620 --> 00:03:30.060
still a total mess.

00:03:47.700 --> 00:03:50.500
(Shirasu Photo Studio)

00:03:59.900 --> 00:04:04.500
(Wataru: The photos are ready.)

00:04:04.593 --> 00:04:07.793
(Minato: Are you free tomorrow night?)

00:04:15.300 --> 00:04:19.800
(Wataru: I have to work.)

00:04:19.900 --> 00:04:23.900
(Minato: Can I see you
before you head home?)

00:04:32.600 --> 00:04:37.600
(September 29, 2025)

00:04:57.430 --> 00:04:58.430
Oh.

00:04:58.440 --> 00:04:59.440
You're here.

00:05:00.190 --> 00:05:01.390
Long time no see.

00:05:01.470 --> 00:05:02.550
Yeah.

00:05:10.490 --> 00:05:11.490
This...

00:05:11.890 --> 00:05:13.230
is a gift for your promotion.

00:05:14.240 --> 00:05:15.240
Why this?

00:05:15.690 --> 00:05:17.790
Because I remember you asking,

00:05:18.470 --> 00:05:20.920
"What does a 'promotion' even mean?"

00:05:21.930 --> 00:05:23.550
I guess I really
didn't understand.

00:05:25.800 --> 00:05:26.800
Thank you.

00:05:28.570 --> 00:05:30.580
Wataru is in the studio.

00:05:32.070 --> 00:05:33.070
I'll wait for him.

00:05:35.260 --> 00:05:36.260
You can just go in.

00:05:57.920 --> 00:05:59.450
Whoa, you scared me!

00:06:00.020 --> 00:06:01.120
Say something next time.

00:06:01.860 --> 00:06:03.680
I didn't want to interrupt.

00:06:10.320 --> 00:06:11.910
What's with the flowers?

00:06:12.830 --> 00:06:14.110
The manager gave them to me.

00:06:14.360 --> 00:06:15.360
A promotion gift.

00:06:15.850 --> 00:06:17.040
Oh.

00:06:18.530 --> 00:06:19.740
They're beautiful.

00:06:20.540 --> 00:06:21.640
What kind are they?

00:06:24.180 --> 00:06:25.260
Wataru.

00:06:41.350 --> 00:06:42.450
Let's take some photos.

00:06:43.080 --> 00:06:44.759
The manager said we can use the studio

00:06:44.760 --> 00:06:46.030
since we're already closed.

00:06:48.390 --> 00:06:49.770
I feel like...

00:06:50.190 --> 00:06:51.790
it's easier to talk while taking photos.

00:07:19.560 --> 00:07:21.070
Go stand in front of the camera.

00:07:46.800 --> 00:07:48.240
Maybe it's the suit,

00:07:48.780 --> 00:07:49.780
but this feels so formal.

00:07:50.540 --> 00:07:51.540
Just me?

00:07:52.170 --> 00:07:53.170
Strike a pose.

00:07:54.200 --> 00:07:55.200
Hey.

00:07:57.750 --> 00:07:58.750
Like this.

00:08:01.510 --> 00:08:02.510
Or like this.

00:08:03.610 --> 00:08:05.050
I'll only do it if you're in it too.

00:08:07.150 --> 00:08:08.310
I have an idea I want to try.

00:08:19.360 --> 00:08:21.130
Okay, get ready.

00:08:29.710 --> 00:08:31.800
This doesn't feel like us at all.

00:08:32.830 --> 00:08:34.090
Give me a bigger smile.

00:08:46.640 --> 00:08:48.200
I should've changed before coming.

00:08:48.580 --> 00:08:49.580
Why?

00:08:49.900 --> 00:08:50.900
We don't match.

00:08:51.830 --> 00:08:54.060
That's what makes it fun.

00:09:06.790 --> 00:09:08.660
That might've been the last one.

00:09:09.460 --> 00:09:10.460
I'll go change the film.

00:09:24.240 --> 00:09:25.240
Wait.

00:09:25.270 --> 00:09:26.590
There's one left.

00:09:32.770 --> 00:09:33.770
Hmm?

00:09:35.800 --> 00:09:37.790
I realized I want to
cherish these feelings.

00:09:38.510 --> 00:09:39.710
Where is this coming from?

00:09:40.080 --> 00:09:41.440
This is the answer I came up with.

00:09:42.790 --> 00:09:44.520
I want to treasure you.

00:09:46.400 --> 00:09:47.500
Well...

00:09:48.290 --> 00:09:49.490
I feel the same way.

00:09:53.050 --> 00:09:54.540
I want happy moments like this

00:09:54.930 --> 00:09:57.490
to last forever.

00:10:01.740 --> 00:10:06.350
Yeah.

00:10:12.370 --> 00:10:13.370
Minato?

00:10:16.630 --> 00:10:18.080
We're best friends.

00:10:20.310 --> 00:10:21.310
Huh?

00:10:23.370 --> 00:10:25.539
Let's stay just like we were.

00:10:25.540 --> 00:10:26.850
Best friends, now and always.

00:10:27.700 --> 00:10:28.980
That's for the best.

00:10:33.850 --> 00:10:34.850
Yeah.

00:10:35.840 --> 00:10:37.040
I think so too.

00:10:43.120 --> 00:10:44.220
Ah.

00:10:51.210 --> 00:10:52.210
That's the last one.

00:10:53.710 --> 00:10:55.010
I'll go let the manager know.

00:11:12.930 --> 00:11:15.270
I'm the one who said we should be friends.

00:11:16.100 --> 00:11:17.880
So why am I so shaken up?

00:11:44.010 --> 00:11:45.010
Well...

00:11:45.390 --> 00:11:46.390
I should get going.

00:11:47.710 --> 00:11:48.710
Okay.

00:11:49.620 --> 00:11:50.620
Oh, right.

00:11:54.620 --> 00:11:55.620
Here.

00:11:55.890 --> 00:11:56.890
The beach photos.

00:11:57.250 --> 00:11:58.250
The ones you took.

00:11:59.860 --> 00:12:00.860
Thanks.

00:12:09.480 --> 00:12:12.090
The beach was really fun.

00:12:14.800 --> 00:12:15.800
Let's go again sometime.

00:12:19.580 --> 00:12:20.580
Sure.

00:12:24.250 --> 00:12:25.250
See ya.

00:12:47.800 --> 00:12:52.800
(October 2, 2025)

00:12:58.500 --> 00:13:01.000
(More cows than people)
(Daichi Yogurt)

00:14:14.250 --> 00:14:15.610
That roll you were shooting

00:14:16.030 --> 00:14:16.980
the other day...

00:14:16.981 --> 00:14:18.110
How did it turn out?

00:14:19.300 --> 00:14:20.300
Oh...

00:14:22.770 --> 00:14:24.910
I haven't checked yet.

00:14:25.770 --> 00:14:27.880
If you're busy, I can develop it for you.

00:14:28.120 --> 00:14:29.930
No, it's fine. I'll do it myself.

00:14:30.170 --> 00:14:31.170
It's important to me.

00:14:32.770 --> 00:14:33.770
I see.

00:14:34.150 --> 00:14:36.680
I'm going to take a break then.

00:14:36.920 --> 00:14:37.990
Okay.

00:14:51.000 --> 00:14:56.200
(Shioiri Kouhei: My birthday
party! I booked the restaurant!)

00:15:00.000 --> 00:15:01.299
(Ebina: Sorry the birthday boy had
to do it.) (Fujisawa: I feel bad about it.)

00:15:01.300 --> 00:15:05.300
(Shioiri Kouhei: It's this
Saturday, don't forget!)

00:15:14.880 --> 00:15:15.880
Minato.

00:15:21.700 --> 00:15:22.900
Heading home?

00:15:25.070 --> 00:15:26.070
Yeah.

00:15:27.220 --> 00:15:28.220
Good work today.

00:15:29.680 --> 00:15:30.680
You too.

00:15:32.720 --> 00:15:34.970
Did you get a gift for Shioiri yet?

00:15:35.580 --> 00:15:37.080
- Not yet.
- Me neither.

00:15:39.260 --> 00:15:40.260
On Saturday,

00:15:40.380 --> 00:15:42.540
want to meet up early and go shopping?

00:15:49.180 --> 00:15:50.180
Sorry.

00:15:50.950 --> 00:15:52.450
I'll probably be running late

00:15:53.090 --> 00:15:54.090
this Saturday.

00:15:58.050 --> 00:16:00.710
Oh, okay. No worries.

00:16:01.640 --> 00:16:02.640
Well... see you then.

00:16:03.680 --> 00:16:05.270
Yeah, see you.

00:16:18.600 --> 00:16:20.700
(October 4, 2025)

00:16:20.780 --> 00:16:23.850
Wait, what happened with that?

00:16:24.370 --> 00:16:25.370
Hmm?

00:16:25.371 --> 00:16:28.130
Didn't you guys start living together?

00:16:28.790 --> 00:16:30.510
That was a year ago.

00:16:31.780 --> 00:16:33.180
And that was it? You just split up?

00:16:33.550 --> 00:16:37.370
Yeah, once the deposit was settled,

00:16:37.690 --> 00:16:39.750
we didn't really plan on seeing each other.

00:16:40.710 --> 00:16:42.830
Wow, that's a total disaster.

00:16:45.120 --> 00:16:48.010
- Why is the mood so heavy?
- Didn't you say you'd start a company?

00:16:48.560 --> 00:16:50.150
Hey, it's my birthday!

00:16:50.770 --> 00:16:52.289
What's going on...

00:16:52.290 --> 00:16:53.569
Wait, what?

00:16:53.570 --> 00:16:54.840
- Seriously?
- Huh?

00:16:54.890 --> 00:16:56.350
So you guys weren't serious?

00:16:59.670 --> 00:17:01.270
We were serious.

00:17:02.523 --> 00:17:04.533
We just messed it up.

00:17:06.610 --> 00:17:08.979
It was over before it even started.

00:17:08.980 --> 00:17:10.120
Come on!

00:17:10.530 --> 00:17:11.930
It's my birthday.

00:17:12.480 --> 00:17:14.500
Let's talk about something happy.

00:17:14.800 --> 00:17:15.640
No, look.

00:17:15.670 --> 00:17:19.400
I'm saying Minato and Wataru are amazing.

00:17:19.610 --> 00:17:20.610
Exactly.

00:17:20.830 --> 00:17:21.830
Huh?

00:17:22.280 --> 00:17:24.910
You lived together
for four years of college

00:17:25.270 --> 00:17:27.170
and you're still this close.

00:17:27.950 --> 00:17:31.980
A bond like that is rare.

00:17:33.720 --> 00:17:35.080
That's because we're best friends.

00:17:36.350 --> 00:17:37.550
I'd expect nothing less.

00:17:39.390 --> 00:17:40.390
How about it?

00:17:40.740 --> 00:17:41.740
Alright.

00:17:42.290 --> 00:17:43.290
To our...

00:17:43.690 --> 00:17:45.350
incredible friendship.

00:17:45.630 --> 00:17:46.730
Cheers!

00:17:47.230 --> 00:17:48.230
Cheers!

00:17:48.400 --> 00:17:49.400
Cheers!

00:17:50.900 --> 00:17:51.900
Cheers!

00:17:53.910 --> 00:17:54.910
Ah.

00:17:55.020 --> 00:17:56.280
By the way, that apartment...

00:17:56.460 --> 00:17:57.380
What are you going to do?

00:17:57.381 --> 00:17:59.940
Oh... we haven't decided yet.

00:18:00.570 --> 00:18:02.120
Good places go fast, you know.

00:18:02.290 --> 00:18:03.450
Let me know if you need help.

00:18:03.680 --> 00:18:05.120
Sure.

00:18:06.530 --> 00:18:08.319
Sorry for the wait, here's your order.

00:18:08.320 --> 00:18:09.709
Oh, sorry, we didn't order this.

00:18:09.710 --> 00:18:11.410
Actually, I did.

00:18:11.690 --> 00:18:13.969
We have to do this again soon!

00:18:13.970 --> 00:18:15.870
How many times are you going to say that?

00:18:17.040 --> 00:18:19.630
It's good, it's good.

00:18:20.890 --> 00:18:23.000
Why do you keep ending with "na"?

00:18:23.640 --> 00:18:26.240
I'll say it as much as I want.

00:18:26.490 --> 00:18:29.040
It'll only get harder to meet up... "ro."

00:18:29.810 --> 00:18:30.810
"Ro"...

00:18:31.350 --> 00:18:34.179
I miss the days we'd run down the halls

00:18:34.180 --> 00:18:36.860
and laugh until we couldn't breathe.

00:18:37.610 --> 00:18:39.010
Wow, that was a smooth transition.

00:18:39.610 --> 00:18:41.810
This whole bit is so boring.

00:18:42.970 --> 00:18:44.570
Alright, I'm heading this way.

00:18:44.763 --> 00:18:47.533
And we're going that way.

00:18:48.470 --> 00:18:49.850
Happy birthday!

00:18:50.530 --> 00:18:51.530
Thanks, guys.

00:18:51.990 --> 00:18:52.990
Get home safe, everyone.

00:18:53.380 --> 00:18:54.500
Don't lose your phone.

00:18:55.070 --> 00:18:56.070
Or your wallet.

00:18:56.960 --> 00:18:58.360
You're the one we're worried about.

00:18:59.840 --> 00:19:01.230
Congrats again! Bye!

00:19:07.480 --> 00:19:08.690
Got a minute?

00:19:12.550 --> 00:19:13.550
Yeah.

00:19:26.550 --> 00:19:27.550
Sit down.

00:19:29.230 --> 00:19:31.690
Usually, people sit on a bench
for this kind of talk.

00:19:49.190 --> 00:19:50.670
Don't you think this is a bit creepy?

00:19:51.400 --> 00:19:53.080
It's faster than I remember.

00:19:54.440 --> 00:19:55.440
This...

00:19:55.510 --> 00:19:56.980
If we go too fast...

00:19:56.990 --> 00:19:58.270
we might not be able to stop.

00:19:59.190 --> 00:20:00.190
That would be a problem.

00:20:00.470 --> 00:20:01.790
If we can't get off...

00:20:11.810 --> 00:20:12.820
Maybe we shouldn't

00:20:13.980 --> 00:20:15.060
see each other for a while.

00:20:16.000 --> 00:20:17.000
What?

00:20:20.640 --> 00:20:22.320
I think there's still time.

00:20:24.430 --> 00:20:26.940
Time for what?

00:20:27.970 --> 00:20:28.970
Wait!

00:20:29.090 --> 00:20:30.090
Minato!

00:20:35.830 --> 00:20:37.030
Why are you running?

00:20:38.480 --> 00:20:42.040
"No"... [TN: He's playing a word game with
the opening syllables of each sentence]

00:20:42.750 --> 00:20:44.930
I'll do what you want.

00:20:45.840 --> 00:20:46.840
Huh?

00:20:47.240 --> 00:20:48.240
It's "Me."

00:20:49.780 --> 00:20:50.790
"Me"?

00:20:51.520 --> 00:20:52.520
"Me"...

00:20:54.390 --> 00:20:55.930
I want to look you in the eye.

00:20:58.070 --> 00:20:59.070
"Do"...

00:21:02.000 --> 00:21:03.720
But I really need time.

00:21:07.890 --> 00:21:09.170
What are you even talking about?

00:21:10.480 --> 00:21:11.480
"Shi"...

00:21:14.000 --> 00:21:15.700
So we can stay best friends.

00:21:16.680 --> 00:21:18.660
I really need some time.

00:21:22.960 --> 00:21:23.960
Minato?

00:21:29.150 --> 00:21:30.150
"To"...

00:21:34.970 --> 00:21:37.000
To... To go back to being just friends.

00:21:37.950 --> 00:21:38.950
I need time.

00:21:42.830 --> 00:21:43.830
Minato...

00:21:45.280 --> 00:21:46.720
We can't see each other for a while.

00:21:50.400 --> 00:21:51.680
Because whenever I'm with you...

00:21:52.650 --> 00:21:54.860
I can't help how much I love you.

00:21:59.010 --> 00:22:00.200
Wait.

00:22:00.970 --> 00:22:02.810
I said wait, Minato!

00:22:17.013 --> 00:22:19.143
Why do you always
decide things on your own?

00:22:38.450 --> 00:22:40.040
I'm in too deep.

00:23:00.080 --> 00:23:01.779
(Next Episode)
I wish I could just split into two people.

00:23:01.780 --> 00:23:04.700
I'm the one who said we should be friends.

00:23:05.120 --> 00:23:06.560
I don't like him anymore...

00:23:06.810 --> 00:23:08.070
Stop thinking about it.

00:23:08.880 --> 00:23:10.080
Stop thinking about him.

00:23:10.300 --> 00:23:12.879
When you can't get
someone out of your head,

00:23:12.880 --> 00:23:14.960
maybe it means you're one
step closer to growing up.